%kryo-spark

class CustomCrossValidator extends org.apache.spark.ml.tuning.CrossValidator {
    import org.apache.spark.mllib.evaluation.BinaryClassificationMetrics
    import org.apache.spark.mllib.util.MLUtils
    import org.apache.spark.sql.{DataFrame, Dataset}
    import com.github.fommil.netlib.F2jBLAS
    import org.apache.spark.ml.param._
    import org.apache.spark.ml.util._
    import org.apache.spark.ml._
    import spark.implicits._
    
    private val f2jBLAS = new F2jBLAS
    
    def customFit[T](train: Dataset[T], validate: Dataset[T]): Tuple2[org.apache.spark.ml.tuning.CrossValidatorModel, Double] = {
        val schema = train.schema
        transformSchema(schema, logging = true)
        val sparkSession = train.sparkSession
        val est = $(estimator)
        val eval = $(evaluator)
        val epm = $(estimatorParamMaps)
        val numModels = epm.length
        val metrics = new Array[Double](epm.length)
        val thresholds = new Array[Double](epm.length)
        val splits = MLUtils.kFold(train.toDF.rdd, $(numFolds), $(seed))
        
        val unbalancedValidationSplits = validate.toDF.randomSplit(Array.fill($(numFolds)) (1.0 / $(numFolds)), $(seed)).map(_.cache)
        
        splits.zipWithIndex.foreach { case ((training, validation), splitIndex) =>
          val trainingDataset = sparkSession.createDataFrame(training, schema).cache()
          val validationDataset = sparkSession.createDataFrame(validation, schema).cache()
          // multi-model training
          logDebug(s"Train split $splitIndex with multiple sets of parameters.")
          val models = est.fit(trainingDataset, epm).asInstanceOf[Seq[Model[_]]]
          trainingDataset.unpersist()
          var i = 0
          while (i < numModels) {
            // TODO: duplicate evaluator to take extra params from input
            val metric = new BinaryClassificationMetrics(models(i).transform(validationDataset.union(unbalancedValidationSplits(splitIndex)), epm(i)).rdd.map(r => (r.getAs[org.apache.spark.ml.linalg.DenseVector]("probability")(1), r.getAs[Double]("manualLabel"))), 1000)
            // threshold for max f1 score
            thresholds(i) += metric.fMeasureByThreshold.max()(Ordering[Double].on(x => x._2))._1 / $(numFolds)
            logDebug(s"Got metric for model trained with ${epm(i)}.")
            metrics(i) += metric.areaUnderPR
            i += 1
          }
          validationDataset.unpersist()
        }
        
        f2jBLAS.dscal(numModels, 1.0 / $(numFolds), metrics, 1)
        logInfo(s"Average cross-validation metrics: ${metrics.toSeq}")
        val (bestMetric, bestIndex) = metrics.zipWithIndex.maxBy(_._1)
        logInfo(s"Best set of parameters:\n${epm(bestIndex)}")
        logInfo(s"Best cross-validation metric: $bestMetric.")
        val bestModel = est.fit(train, epm(bestIndex)).asInstanceOf[Model[_]]
        val bestThreshold = thresholds(bestIndex)
        val constructor = classOf[org.apache.spark.ml.tuning.CrossValidatorModel].getConstructors()(0)
        constructor.setAccessible(true)
        
        (copyValues(constructor.newInstance(uid, bestModel, metrics).asInstanceOf[org.apache.spark.ml.tuning.CrossValidatorModel].setParent(this)), bestThreshold)
    }
}

import org.apache.spark.ml.tuning.ParamGridBuilder
import org.apache.spark.ml.param.ParamMap
import org.apache.spark.ml.evaluation.BinaryClassificationEvaluator
import org.apache.spark.sql.Dataset
import org.apache.spark.ml.{Estimator, Model}

def tune[T <: Model[T], D](estimator: Estimator[T], grid: Array[ParamMap], train: Dataset[D], validate: Dataset[D]): Tuple2[T, Double] = {
    val result = new CustomCrossValidator()
        .setNumFolds(4)
        .setEvaluator(new BinaryClassificationEvaluator())
        .setEstimator(estimator)
        .setEstimatorParamMaps(grid)
        .customFit(train, validate)
    
    (result._1.bestModel.asInstanceOf[T], result._2)
}

def naiveBayes[T](tr: Dataset[T], vl: Dataset[T], tst: Dataset[T]): Tuple4[Double, Double, Double, Double] = {
    import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.MinMaxScaler
    import org.apache.spark.ml.classification.{NaiveBayes, NaiveBayesModel}
    
    val probScaler = new MinMaxScaler()
        .setInputCol("scaledFeatures")
        .setOutputCol("probScaledFeatures")
        .setMin(0.001)
        .setMax(1.0)
        .fit(tr)
    
    val probTrainingData = probScaler.transform(tr)
    val probValidationData = probScaler.transform(vl)
    val probTestData = probScaler.transform(tst)
    
    val model = new NaiveBayes()
        .setLabelCol("manualLabel")
        .setFeaturesCol("probScaledFeatures")
    
    val paramGrid = new ParamGridBuilder()
        .addGrid(model.smoothing, Array(0.01, 0.1, 1.0, 10.0, 100.0))
        .build()
    
    val (tuned, threshold) = tune(model, paramGrid, probTrainingData, probValidationData)
    
    println("Smoothing: " + tuned.asInstanceOf[NaiveBayesModel].getSmoothing)
    
    eval(tuned, threshold, probTestData)
}

def randomForest[T](tr: Dataset[T], vl: Dataset[T], tst: Dataset[T]): Tuple4[Double, Double, Double, Double] = {
    import org.apache.spark.ml.classification.{RandomForestClassifier, RandomForestClassificationModel}
    
    val model = new RandomForestClassifier()
        .setLabelCol("manualLabel")
        .setFeaturesCol("scaledFeatures")
    
    val paramGrid = new ParamGridBuilder()
        .addGrid(model.impurity, Array("gini"))
        .addGrid(model.maxBins, Array(32, 64))
        .addGrid(model.maxDepth, Array(7))
        .addGrid(model.minInfoGain, Array(0.0, 0.001))
        .addGrid(model.minInstancesPerNode, Array(1, 2))
        .addGrid(model.numTrees, Array(20))
        .addGrid(model.subsamplingRate, Array(0.5, 1.0))
        .build()
        
    val (tuned, threshold) = tune(model, paramGrid, tr, vl)
        
    println("Impurity " + tuned.asInstanceOf[RandomForestClassificationModel].getImpurity)
    println("Max Bins: " + tuned.asInstanceOf[RandomForestClassificationModel].getMaxBins)
    println("Max Depth: " + tuned.asInstanceOf[RandomForestClassificationModel].getMaxDepth)
    println("Min Info Gain: " + tuned.asInstanceOf[RandomForestClassificationModel].getMinInfoGain)
    println("Min Instances per Node: " + tuned.asInstanceOf[RandomForestClassificationModel].getMinInstancesPerNode)
    println("Num Trees: " + tuned.asInstanceOf[RandomForestClassificationModel].getNumTrees)
    println("Subsampling Rate: " + tuned.asInstanceOf[RandomForestClassificationModel].getSubsamplingRate)
    
    eval(tuned, threshold, tst)
}

import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.MinMaxScaler
import org.apache.spark.ml.classification.{NaiveBayes, NaiveBayesModel}

val probScaler = new MinMaxScaler()
    .setInputCol("scaledFeatures")
    .setOutputCol("probScaledFeatures")
    .setMin(0.001)
    .setMax(1.0)
    .fit(train)

val probTrainingData = probScaler.transform(train)
val probTestData = probScaler.transform(test)

val nb1 = new NaiveBayes()
    .setLabelCol("manualLabel")
    .setFeaturesCol("probScaledFeatures")
    .setSmoothing(10.0)
    .fit(probTrainingData)
    .transform(probTestData)
    .rdd
    .map(r => (r.getAs[org.apache.spark.ml.linalg.DenseVector]("probability")(1), r.getAs[Double]("manualLabel")))

val nb1metrics = new BinaryClassificationMetrics(nb1, 1000)
nb1metrics.areaUnderPR
println("\nthreshold;rec;pre\n1.0000000000;0.0000000000;1.0000000000")
nb1metrics.recallByThreshold.zip(nb1metrics.precisionByThreshold).filter(t => t._1._1 == t._2._1).map(t => (t._1._1, t._1._2, t._2._2)).collect.foreach(t => println("%.10f;%.10f;%.10f".format(t._1, t._2, t._3)))
